name: Pizza
description: A savory dish of Italian origin consisting of a flat, round base of dough baked with a topping of tomatoes and cheese, often with added meat, vegetables, or other ingredients.

name: Burger
description: A sandwich consisting of one or more cooked patties of ground meat, placed inside a sliced bread roll or bun. Often served with lettuce, tomato, and condiments.

name: Sushi
description: A Japanese dish consisting of vinegared rice accompanied by various ingredients such as seafood, vegetables, and occasionally tropical fruits.

name: Pasta
description: An Italian dish made from unleavened dough of wheat flour mixed with water, formed into sheets or other shapes, and cooked by boiling or baking.

name: Tacos
description: A traditional Mexican dish consisting of a small hand-sized corn or wheat tortilla topped with a filling such as beef, chicken, vegetables, or seafood.

name: Ice Cream
description: A sweetened frozen food typically eaten as a snack or dessert, made from dairy products such as milk and cream, combined with flavorings and sweeteners.

name: Ramen
description: A Japanese noodle soup consisting of Chinese-style wheat noodles served in a meat- or fish-based broth, often flavored with soy sauce or miso.

name: Samosa
description: A fried or baked pastry with a savory filling, such as spiced potatoes, onions, peas, or lentils. It is popular in South Asia, the Middle East, and Africa.

name: Fried Chicken
description: Chicken pieces that have been coated in seasoned batter and fried until crisp. It is a staple of Southern cuisine in the United States.

name: Dosa
description: A thin, crispy pancake originating from South India, made from a fermented batter of rice and black gram, often served with chutney and sambar.

name: Pav Bhaji
description: A fast food dish from India consisting of a thick vegetable curry, served with a soft bread roll known as pav.

name: Chow Mein
description: A Chinese stir-fried noodle dish with vegetables and sometimes meat or tofu, often seasoned with soy sauce and garlic.

name: Dim Sum
description: A variety of bite-sized Cantonese dishes traditionally served in small steamer baskets or on small plates, typically enjoyed with tea.

name: Falafel
description: A Middle Eastern dish of deep-fried ball or patty made from ground chickpeas or fava beans, often served in a pita or flatbread.

name: Pad Thai
description: A stir-fried rice noodle dish commonly served as street food in Thailand, often made with shrimp, chicken, or tofu, and flavored with tamarind.

name: Poutine
description: A Canadian dish consisting of French fries topped with cheese curds and gravy, originating from the province of Quebec.

name: Biryani
description: A mixed rice dish originating among the Muslims of the Indian subcontinent, made with spices, rice, and meat, usually chicken or mutton.

name: Shawarma
description: A Middle Eastern dish consisting of thinly sliced pieces of meat, typically lamb or chicken, stacked in a cone shape and roasted on a vertical rotisserie.

name: Pho
description: A Vietnamese soup consisting of broth, rice noodles, herbs, and meat, typically made with either beef or chicken.

name: Churros
description: A fried-dough pastry that originated in Spain and Portugal, often sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon, and sometimes served with hot chocolate for dipping.
